      • addedInSource

        public Object addedInSource(org.eclipse.emf.cdo.common.revision.CDORevision sourceRevision,
                            Map<org.eclipse.emf.cdo.common.id.CDOID,Object> targetMap)
        Checks if the specified CDORevision from the source change set conflicts with any changes on the target.

        The default case will allow the add by returning sourceRevision (a CDORevision).

        SNOMED CT-specific conflict processing will report a conflict if:

        • a new object on target has the same SNOMED CT component identifier as the new object on source
        • a detached object on target is referenced by the new object on source
        The addition is allowed through in all other cases.
        Specified by:
        addedInSource in interface ICDOConflictProcessor
        Overrides:
        addedInSource in class AbstractCDOConflictProcessor
        Parameters:
        sourceRevision - the new CDORevision from the source change set
        targetMap - the computed change set for the target branch, indexed by CDOID
        Returns:
        • null if the add should be ignored;
        • a CDORevision if an addition should take place;
        • a CDOID if an object should be removed;
        • a DefaultCDOMerger.Conflict if a merge conflict should be reported.
